<br>
I am going to be consolidating the galleries more, separating it only by fantasy vs mainstream and, within that, color vs. b&w.  Or that's the plan, anyway. :)  I will be moving the little texty bits to the page the pictures themselves are on, rather than being on the index page.<br>
<br>
What I can't decide is whether to keep the pics in a pop-up window (because pop-ups have always kind of annoyed me) ... I'm leaning toward 'no'.  If I don't, they'll most likely load in the frame where the thumbnails are displayed, and the viewer will just have to make use of the 'back' button, which we do for most folks' galleries, anyway. :)  I think I just answered my question.<br>
<br>
But just in case, are there any other suggestions?  Things I oughta add or which are completely unnecessary? <p>--<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->~Gweenie<br>
